1
00:00:00,416 --> 00:00:02,791
Interviewer: Were you tortured? Did you experience torture?

2
00:00:02,916 --> 00:00:03,916
Only flogging

3
00:00:04,416 --> 00:00:07,250
Interviewer: Before the flogging, any other torture?

4
00:00:07,541 --> 00:00:12,000
No, they didn’t torture me, just flogging at that time

5
00:00:12,375 --> 00:00:14,250
Interviewer: Were there torture rooms?

6
00:00:14,416 --> 00:00:16,791
Yes, they had torture rooms in this place

7
00:00:17,333 --> 00:00:20,833
Interviewer: Were there prisoners with you who were taken for torture and brought back?

8
00:00:20,916 --> 00:00:22,125
Yes, many prisoners

9
00:00:22,416 --> 00:00:26,125
They took them for torture, and they beat them unbelievably

10
00:00:26,541 --> 00:00:28,750
Interviewer: They were with you in the same room? Witness: In the same room

11
00:00:28,833 --> 00:00:31,583
Some were moved to other rooms, and some were taken again

12
00:00:31,750 --> 00:00:35,541
Interviewer: The people you were close to, when they were taken for torture

13
00:00:35,750 --> 00:00:39,458
And brought back again, didn’t they tell you about the torture methods?

14
00:00:39,583 --> 00:00:44,375
The ones used on them, like the <i>falaqa</i> [foot whipping], flogging, electricity, or the <i>mazaref</i> [body piercing]?

15
00:00:44,458 --> 00:00:46,625
Everything, there were people they used everything on

16
00:00:47,083 --> 00:00:50,958
They would walk in on their feet, and return carried in a blanket

17
00:00:53,041 --> 00:00:54,375
Interviewer: Did they have torture marks?

18
00:00:54,458 --> 00:00:58,541
Yes, they showed torture marks, but as I told you before

19
00:00:59,041 --> 00:01:02,208
You couldn’t ask, What’s your story, what happened to you, and so on

20
00:01:02,375 --> 00:01:04,250
Interviewer: I mean, did they bring them back after torture?

21
00:01:04,541 --> 00:01:08,208
Was it obvious they had been tortured by skinning? Or flogging?

22
00:01:08,291 --> 00:01:11,000
Or with electricity, or hanging, and so on?

23
00:01:11,083 --> 00:01:13,583
No, there was electricity, and they hit them with a stick

24
00:01:13,916 --> 00:01:17,000
I mean their body was crushed, they hit them with a metal pipe

25
00:01:17,541 --> 00:01:20,250
Interviewer: Do you have a story about one of the people who was with you

26
00:01:20,375 --> 00:01:21,791
About the torture method used on him?

27
00:01:21,875 --> 00:01:24,125
They would take him for two or three days

28
00:01:24,166 --> 00:01:26,458
But it never happened to me

29
00:01:27,333 --> 00:01:29,291
Interviewer: It didn’t happen in front of you?
Witness: No, by God

30
00:01:29,750 --> 00:01:32,916
That’s according to what I had heard, that’s how it was

31
00:01:34,041 --> 00:01:37,083
Interviewer: At night, when you were in the room

32
00:01:37,166 --> 00:01:39,500
Did you hear screams of people being tortured?

33
00:01:40,166 --> 00:01:44,083
Yes, that happens, killing and screams

34
00:01:44,541 --> 00:01:45,916
But where did it come from? You don’t know

35
00:01:46,166 --> 00:01:47,583
Interviewer: Were the screams close or far?

36
00:01:47,666 --> 00:01:51,000
No, it wasn’t very far, I mean

37
00:01:53,625 --> 00:01:56,125
Interviewer: So do you think it was from the rooms next to you?

38
00:01:56,500 --> 00:02:00,458
I think so, and I’m sure they had a place for killing and torture

39
00:02:00,500 --> 00:02:03,750
Interviewer: Was the screaming clear?
Witness: Yes, clear, and loud screams

40
00:02:04,291 --> 00:02:05,916
Interviewer: All night or at a specific time?

41
00:02:06,250 --> 00:02:09,958
At night and in the early morning, this happens

42
00:02:10,791 --> 00:02:12,916
I heard about many who died under their torture

43
00:02:13,625 --> 00:02:16,250
Many people died during torture

44
00:02:19,083 --> 00:02:24,000
Interviewer: Are you saying, or did you hear, that they died from torture?

45
00:02:24,125 --> 00:02:25,833
What kinds of torture did they use?

46
00:02:26,125 --> 00:02:27,666
They tortured them in many ways

47
00:02:27,958 --> 00:02:30,583
Many, anything you can think of in torture

48
00:02:33,041 --> 00:02:34,791
Interviewer: About how many people?

49
00:02:35,125 --> 00:02:36,625
They tortured many people

50
00:02:37,750 --> 00:02:40,791
Many died from torture, and many collapsed from torture

51
00:02:40,916 --> 00:02:42,666
And many suffered other things because of torture

52
00:02:43,833 --> 00:02:47,833
There are people to this day who suffer illnesses as a result of torture

53
00:02:49,125 --> 00:02:52,083
Some got diabetes, some got high blood pressure, or had a stroke

54
00:02:52,458 --> 00:02:53,750
And some even got cancer
